# AWS S3 Presigned URL Upload API

## 🚀 Features

- Upload files directly to S3 using presigned URLs
- Secure file handling without passing files through backend
- UUID-based file naming to prevent overwrites
- Supports upload and download via signed URLs

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Node.js (TypeScript)
- AWS Lambda
- AWS S3
- API Gateway

## 🔄 Flow

1. Client sends file metadata (name, type) to Lambda  
2. Lambda generates presigned upload & download URLs  
3. Client uploads file directly to S3 using PUT request  
4. File can be downloaded using presigned GET URL  

## 📦 Setup (Local)

```bash
npm install
npx tsc
```

## ☁️ Deployment

### 1. Build project

```bash
npx tsc
```

### 2. Zip compiled files

```bash
zip -r function.zip dist node_modules package.json
```

### 3. Upload to AWS Lambda

### 4. Set environment variables in Lambda

```env
S3_BUCKET_NAME=your-bucket-name
REGION=your-region
```

### 5. Configure API Gateway trigger

## 🧪 Testing

- Call API (POST) to generate URLs  
- Use `uploadUrl` with PUT request (binary file upload)  
- Use `downloadUrl` to download file  

## 📌 Notes

- Uses AWS SDK v3  
- Uses UUID for unique file naming  
- Ensure `Content-Type` matches during upload  
- Presigned URLs expire after a limited time  

## 📂 Project Structure

```text
src/
  handler.ts
  presignedUrl.ts

package.json
